In this press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs addresses two topics: the Israeli raid on the aid ship headed to Gaza, and the ongoing oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico. Regarding the raid, Gibbs states that the United States supports the international community's condemnation of the loss of life and injuries resulting from the Israeli military operation. He also calls for a prompt, impartial, credible, and transparent investigation into the incident. Regarding the oil spill, Gibbs acknowledges the frustration and heartbreak caused by the ongoing situation. He mentions that the latest attempt to contain the well involves a procedure called the top cap. He also emphasizes that the President is enraged by the time it has taken to address the spill and that the administration is doing everything possible to plug the leak and respond to the pollution.